# Design Ops Kit — Windsurf Rules
# Generated from skills + knowledge-base
# Copy to your project root as .windsurfrules

## Design system
- NEVER use Material UI (@mui/*), Chakra UI (@chakra-ui/*), or shadcn
- All components MUST conform to Layer 2 contracts in knowledge-base/design-system/contracts/
- All visual values MUST reference design tokens — never hardcode colors, spacing, font sizes
- Read the contract schema: knowledge-base/design-system/contracts/_contract-schema.md

## When building components
1. Load the component contract first
2. Implement all 7 dimensions (API, visual, a11y, composition, behavior, rules, platform)
3. Include all states from Dimension 5 (idle, hover, focus, active, loading, disabled)
4. Accessible by default per Dimension 3
5. Co-locate tests

## When reviewing code
1. Check contract compliance (props, types, defaults)
2. Check token discipline (no hardcoded values)
3. Check blocked packages
4. Check accessibility requirements from contract

## Skill reference
For complex tasks, reference the relevant skill in skills/ for detailed process.
For chains (multi-step workflows), see orchestration/chains/.

## Context management
- Load knowledge files conditionally — don't read everything
- Between multi-step tasks, produce structured summaries not full replays
- If context feels bloated (>40K tokens of history), start a new session with a handoff doc
